==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sperrylite
<hw>Sper"ry*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos><ety>[Named after F. L.
<ets>Sperry</ets>, who discovered it.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>An
arsenide of platinum occurring in grains and minute isometric crystals
of tin-white color. It is found near Sudbury, Ontario Canada, and is the
only known compound of platinum occurring in nature.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

